      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AMRON SAMMY (8) was a winner two back in fast time when racing on speed but drifted back latest and safely held when 7th and beaten 15 lengths at Traralgon (25.08). Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from seven starts. Should bounce back. CROSS LOCKS (2) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing third (26.32) at this track over 460m. Hard to beat again. PABLO VENDETTA (7) is having his first start around this course. Impressive winner latest at Horsham in a Grade 4/5 in quickest time of the program (27.23). Has definite claims. DAVE (5) is in the mix after placing here at this trip last time out.",
